01:12:27,948 --> 01:12:28,629
Thank you, Council Member.

1009
01:12:28,649 --> 01:12:29,510
Council Member Marks.

1010
01:12:30,668 --> 01:12:31,528
Thank you, Mr. President.

1011
01:12:31,548 --> 01:12:39,631
I want to thank Mr. Varnberg for bringing this issue up, because I know we've all been contacted by Meffitt residents that are equally as concerned.

1012
01:12:40,771 --> 01:12:46,293
I need to say over the last three or four weeks, this issue has evolved many times.

1013
01:12:46,993 --> 01:12:52,235
And I think originally, if we all remember, the issue was don't wear mask.

1014
01:12:52,375 --> 01:12:54,875
Remember when it first came out, they said mask won't help you.

1015
01:12:55,376 --> 01:12:59,617
And don't wear mask and leave the mask for the health care professionals.

1016
01:13:00,163 --> 01:13:09,813
the first responders, and then it evolved into, as more information came in, that it is helpful to have a mask and to reduce the risks like Councilor Beers mentioned.

1017
01:13:10,453 --> 01:13:21,344
I think there's a lot of misinformation out there that people believe if they, as long as they stay a social distance of six feet, in particular outside, there's no need for a mask.

1018
01:13:21,824 --> 01:13:24,247
And I think that's where a lot of the misinformation lies.

1019
01:13:25,087 --> 01:13:32,354
that now that has also evolved and your footprint, so called footprint is left behind.

1020
01:13:33,095 --> 01:13:34,476
And that's critical.

1021
01:13:34,837 --> 01:13:38,540
I just want to say to that mask is one aspect of PPE.

1022
01:13:38,941 --> 01:13:40,062
There's also gloves.

1023
01:13:41,185 --> 01:13:47,627
The disease is transmitted through droplets and so forth, but it's also transmitted through touch.

1024
01:13:48,467 --> 01:14:00,210
And you could be somewhere with a mask on, touch a surface, and then put that fingers to your eyes, to your nose, to your mouth after the fact.

1025
01:14:00,810 --> 01:14:02,031
and catch to the disease.

1026
01:14:02,451 --> 01:14:06,793
So if you don't protect your hands as well as your face, you're equally as vulnerable.

1027
01:14:06,853 --> 01:14:09,594
So whatever we do, I think we have to look at all aspects.

1028
01:14:10,054 --> 01:14:17,398
And in my opinion, I think it should be the wearing of gloves as well, the rubber gloves when you're out in public for now.

1029
01:14:18,278 --> 01:14:21,900
So I think education, as the chief of staff mentioned,

1030
01:14:22,300 --> 01:14:23,420
is extremely important.

1031
01:14:23,761 --> 01:14:30,783
The fact that Councilor Morrell and Councilor Caviello mentioned that not everyone, I had to make homemade face masks.

1032
01:14:31,263 --> 01:14:32,804
And it took quite some time to do it.

1033
01:14:33,204 --> 01:14:35,825
Everyone says, oh, look online, you make a quick, easy one.

1034
01:14:36,265 --> 01:14:38,106
They're not quick, easy, at least for me.

1035
01:14:38,406 --> 01:14:39,907
And I consider myself pretty handy.

1036
01:14:40,227 --> 01:14:41,307
They're not quick and easy.

1037
01:14:41,607 --> 01:14:45,108
And they don't fit right, they push your nose in, you can't breathe.

1038
01:14:45,389 --> 01:14:48,830
So there's a lot more than just making a quick homemade mask.

1039
01:14:49,330 --> 01:15:00,179
And I think if we can get these masks out to the general public, like was mentioned in Somerville and so forth, I think that'll go a long way for people that will have them near their front door, like I do.

1040
01:15:00,219 --> 01:15:03,882
Every time I go out, boom, it goes on automatically because it's right there.

1041
01:15:04,723 --> 01:15:07,525
But if I didn't have one in the house, who knows?

1042
01:15:08,266 --> 01:15:13,190
So I think the first thing for prevention is to make sure that these are out there.

1043
01:15:13,818 --> 01:15:17,999
And I don't know what we can do to get these masks and rubber gloves out there.

1044
01:15:18,059 --> 01:15:20,220
But I think that should be our first thing.

1045
01:15:21,040 --> 01:15:24,661
I don't like the concept of penalizing people, to be quite frank.

1046
01:15:25,261 --> 01:15:29,422
I know some communities of 200, 300 old fines for not wearing a mask.

1047
01:15:31,003 --> 01:15:32,303
I don't like that concept.

1048
01:15:32,910 --> 01:15:38,572
I think you have to get people to comply in a way that you reason with them and say, hey, you know what?

1049
01:15:38,733 --> 01:15:41,314
This is a concern for safety, concern for health.

1050
01:15:41,714 --> 01:15:54,219
Now we're hearing over in England and so forth that they're saying that kids are coming down with some sort of disease from the COVID that they didn't

1051
01:15:54,563 --> 01:15:55,944
think they were susceptible to.

1052
01:15:56,344 --> 01:15:59,366
This is brand new and they're starting to get cases over there.

1053
01:16:00,266 --> 01:16:03,768
You hear animals now, dogs, cats, you know.

1054
01:16:04,255 --> 01:16:09,097
So this is something that we really have to take the initiative.

1055
01:16:09,437 --> 01:16:16,440
